  <h1>What's wrong with AI?</h1>

  <p>With the rise of consumer facing systems, AI, has the potential to combat or spread new forms of discrimination, through fundamental choices in representation, design and development. How can we positively inform AI design by recognizing cultural and social assumptions and biases that lead to discrimination?</p>

